section_text: 35 1 . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . .  2 A warrant given by the Bank for the payment of any cash bonus payable on behalf of His Majesty’s Government in consideration of any offer made for the exchange of any Government stock shall be deemed to be a cheque within the meaning of the  Bills of Exchange Act 1882, . . .  3 . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . .  4 In this section the expressions “ Government stock ” and “ the Bank ” have the same meaning as they have for the purposes of Part V of the  Finance Act 1921.

38 1 This Act may be cited as the Finance Act 1939. 2 . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . .  3 . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . .  4 . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . .  5 Any reference in this Act to any other enactment shall, unless the contrary is expressly provided or the context otherwise requires, be construed as a reference to that enactment as amended by any subsequent enactment, including this Act. 6 . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . .  7 Such of the provisions of this Act as relate to matters with respect to which the Parliament of Northern Ireland has power to make laws shall not extend to Northern Ireland.
